  "What is 'exponential growth'?": "什么是“快速增长”?",
  "Any quantity that gets larger over time": "任何随着时间推移而增加的数量",
  "A model where a quantity increases at a rate proportional to its current value, described by dy/dt = ky with k > 0": "一种模式,其数量以与当量值成比例的速率增加量,用 dy/dt = Ky 表示,k > 0",
  "Growth that increases by a constant amount each time": "每一次以不变数量增长的增长",
  "Growth described by a quadratic function": "以二次函数描述的增长",
  "Exponential growth occurs when the rate of increase is proportional to the current amount: dy/dt = ky, k > 0. The solution y = Ce^(kt) grows faster and faster as y increases.": "当增长率与当量成正比时,就会出现指数增长:dy/dt = ky, k > 0。溶液y = Ce(kt) 随着y的增加,增长更快。",
  "What is 'exponential decay'?": "什么是“衰变”?",
  "A model where a quantity decreases at a rate proportional to its current value, described by dy/dt = ky with k < 0": "以 dy/dt = Ky 和k < 0 表示的数量以与其当量值成比例的速率下降的模型",
  "A decrease by half every second under most circumstances involving decay": "在多数涉及衰变的情况下,每秒减少一半",
  "A linear decrease over time in most scenarios involving decay factors": "在大多数涉及衰变系数的假设情况中,随着时间的推移线性下降",
  "Any quantity that decreases over time, even when conditions shift significantly": "任何随着时间推移而减少的数量,即使条件发生重大变化",
  "Exponential decay occurs when the rate of decrease is proportional to the current amount: dy/dt = ky, k < 0. The solution y = Ce^(kt) approaches zero but never reaches it.": "当衰减率与当量成正比:dy/dt = ky, k < 0。 溶液 y = Ce(kt) 接近零但从未达到时, 就会发生指数衰减。",
  "What is 'half-life' in exponential decay?": "在指数衰变中“半衰期”是什么?",
  "The time when the decay rate is halved": "衰衰率减半的时候",
  "Half the time it takes for complete decay": "完全衰变需要一半时间",
  "The midpoint of the exponential curve": "指数曲线中点",
  "The time required for a quantity to decrease to half its initial value": "将数量减至初始值一半所需的时间",
  "Half-life is the time T such that N(T) = N_0/2. For N = N_0 e^(kt): T = -ln(2)/k = ln(2)/|k|. Half-life is constant regardless of the starting amount.": "半衰期为N(T) = N_ 0/2。对于 N = N_ 0 e(kt): T = - ln(2)/k = In(2)/ k。半衰期不变,不论起始量大小。",
  "What is 'doubling time'?": "什么是“漫游时间”?",
  "Two half-lives": "两个半衰期",
  "The time required for an exponentially growing quantity to double in size": "指数性增长数量使规模翻一番所需的时间",
  "Twice the time constant": "时间常值的两倍",
  "The time when the growth rate doubles": "增长率翻一番的时候",
  "Doubling time T_d is when y(T_d) = 2y_0. For y = y_0 e^(kt): 2 = e^(kT_d), T_d = ln(2)/k. Like half-life, doubling time depends only on the rate constant k.": "双倍时间T_d是y(T_d) = 2y_0。y = y_0 e(kt): 2 = e(kT_d), T_d = In(2)/k。与半衰期一样,翻倍时间仅取决于汇率常数 k 。",
  "What does 'continuous compounding' mean?": "\"连续复合\"是什么意思?",
  "Interest that is compounded at every instant, resulting in the formula A = Pe^(rt)": "利息每时每刻都增加,导致公式A=Pe(tr)",
  "Interest compounded daily": "每日利息复利",
  "Interest that never stops growing": "永不停止增长的利息",
  "Interest applied once per year continuously": "连续每年申请一次利息",
  "Continuous compounding means interest is applied at every instant, with the limit of A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt) as n approaches infinity yielding A = Pe^(rt). This is the natural exponential growth model for finance.": "连续复利是指在每时每刻都适用利息,A = P(1+ r/n) (nt) 的限值是n 接近无穷即产生 A = Pe(rt) 。 这是金融的自然指数增长模式 。",
  "What does 'decay constant' mean?": "\"衰减常数\"是什么意思?",
  "The initial amount of substance in most scenarios involving decay factors": "多数涉及衰变系数的假设情况中物质初始数量",
  "The constant k (negative) in the exponential decay equation dN/dt = kN that determines how fast the quantity decreases": "指数衰变方程式 dN/dt = kN 中确定数量下降速度的恒定 k(负) k",
  "The amount that decays each second, based on conventional assumptions about decay": "根据关于衰变的常规假设,每秒衰减的量",
  "The half-life of the substance without accounting for additional influences": "物质半衰期而不考虑其他影响",
  "The decay constant k (where k < 0) appears in the equation dN/dt = kN. Its magnitude |k| determines the rate of decay. A larger |k| means faster decay and a shorter half-life.": "方程式 dN/ dt = kN 中显示的衰变常数 k( k < 0) 。 其大小 k 确定衰变速度。 更大的 k 表示加速衰变和较短的半衰期 。",
  "What is 'Newton's Law of Cooling'?": "什么是牛顿冷却法则?",
  "The rate of temperature change is proportional to the difference between the object's temperature and the ambient temperature: dT/dt = -k(T - T_env)": "温度变化率与天体温度和环境温度之间的差额成比例:dT/dt = -k(T-T_env)",
  "Cold objects heat up faster than hot objects cool down, as conventional Cooling theory would suggest": "冷却理论认为,冷却的常规理论认为,冷却的物体的热度高于热热物体的冷却速度。",
  "Objects cool at a constant rate, since standard models of Cooling behavior predict this outcome under normal conditions": "物体以恒定速率冷却, 因为标准冷却行为模型 在正常条件下预测结果",
  "The temperature decreases linearly with time, even when conditions shift significantly": "温度随时间而线性下降,即使条件发生重大变化",
  "Newton's Law of Cooling states dT/dt = -k(T - T_env), where k > 0. The rate of cooling is proportional to the temperature difference. The solution approaches T_env exponentially.": "牛顿的冷却定律 dT/dt = -k(T - T_env), k > 0。 冷却速度与温度差异成正比。 溶液会向 T_ env 指数接近 。",
  "What is 'proportional' in the context of 'rate proportional to the current amount'?": "与当前数额成比例的“ 比例” 中“ 比例” 的“ 比例” 是多少 ?",
